        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 4:51PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 451 PM EDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
strong thunderstorm over Cordele, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail, frequent cloud to
ground lightning and increased chance of a brief tornado.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...While winds should result in minor damage to tree limbs
and blowing around of light, unsecured objects, this
storm has also exhibited localized rotation. A brief
tornado could quickly form.

Locations impacted include...
Cordele, Rochelle, Arabi, Pitts, East Crisp, Georgia Veterans
Memorial St Pk, Raines, Double Run, Wenona, Seville, and Hatley.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
central and west central Georgia.</instruction>
